Preheat your oven to 200°C. Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and @cider vinegar{15%ml} into a #medium bowl. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and mix together. Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and sweetcorn to the mayo mixture, mix again and set aside. Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%tin} in a sieve.

Pop the wedges on a low sided wide #baking tray in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Meanwhile, pop the @tomato passata{1%tin}, cannelini beans and @water{50%ml} into a #pan and pop on medium heat. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and stir in the @BBQ sauce{64%ml}. Taste and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Remove from the heat and set aside.

Heat ½ cm of @vegetable oil{} in a #frying pan on medium high heat. While the oil heats up, put the @plain flour{32%g} in a #bowl with the @water{32%ml} and @Cajun spice mix{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Mix together, then add the @British chicken thighs{4} and turn to coat in the mixture.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the floured chicken pieces in the hot oil and fry until
golden brown and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes} total. Turn the chicken every
~{2-3%minutes} and cook in batches of necessary.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Reheat the beans until piping hot. Serve the chicken, beans, slaw and wedges at
the table with the @tomato ketchup{1%tbsp} on the side for dipping your chips
in, dig in!